This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with monocular 6D pose estimation from images. It also involves deep learning, which is a common technique used in computer vision research. 

It is also likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the proposed method has potential applications in robotics, where robots need to work with hundreds of different objects in a real environment. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new loss formulation that directly optimizes over all parameters using deep learning. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the proposed method involves using deep learning to estimate object pose and shape, which is a common task in AI research. 

Finally, the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is a possibility as the proposed method involves rendering 3D point clouds, which is a common task in computer graphics research.
